There we go.

00:31:59.528 --> 00:32:02.368
Next up, let's talk
about theme-level issues.

00:32:04.108 --> 00:32:06.959
Theme-level issues on a WordPress site

00:32:07.710 --> 00:32:10.919
may include default text color
that results

00:32:10.920 --> 00:32:12.660
in insufficient color contrast.

00:32:13.346 --> 00:32:16.470
This would be text
on multiple pages throughout your site.

00:32:17.669 --> 00:32:20.159
Another theme-level issue
could be inline links,

00:32:20.160 --> 00:32:22.799
which is links
in the middle of a paragraph that use

00:32:22.829 --> 00:32:26.159
color alone to visually indicate
that they are interactive.

00:32:26.910 --> 00:32:29.549
Typically, if you have links
in the middle of a paragraph,

00:32:29.850 --> 00:32:31.888
you want to make sure that they have
underlines so that users

00:32:31.889 --> 00:32:35.939
can easily see that,
"Hey, that's an interactive control."

00:32:37.199 --> 00:32:39.899
That is typically set
as a style at the theme-level,

00:32:40.139 --> 00:32:43.059
and so if there's an issue with that,
that's probably a theme-level issue.

00:32:44.850 --> 00:32:47.908
Other theme-level issues
can include really anything in your header

00:32:47.909 --> 00:32:50.309
or your footer or perhaps even
in your sidebars,

00:32:51.270 --> 00:32:53.249
common components
that are repeated throughout

00:32:53.250 --> 00:32:54.446
your whole site.

00:32:54.764 --> 00:32:59.129
Those are probably the archetypical
examples of theme-level issues,

00:32:59.130 --> 00:33:01.276
anything in your footer or header.

00:33:03.197 --> 00:33:06.557
Here, let's look
at a theme-level issue on the site.

