00:40:06.980 --> 00:40:09.210
Essentially, one thing
which is really useful

00:40:09.539 --> 00:40:12.150
in some code editors
like Visual Studio Code

00:40:12.479 --> 00:40:18.930
is you can actually search
for text within not just one file,

00:40:19.050 --> 00:40:20.400
but across a whole directory.

00:40:20.879 --> 00:40:22.559
In this case, in Visual Studio Code,

00:40:23.610 --> 00:40:25.859
I opened up the folder
for the parent theme,

00:40:26.100 --> 00:40:29.490
and I knew there was an issue
with this particular CSS selector,

00:40:30.360 --> 00:40:31.859
the class small part.

00:40:32.279 --> 00:40:35.608
I searched for that CSS selector,
and then it took me right

00:40:35.609 --> 00:40:39.840
to that style.css
and showed me where that was.

00:40:40.290 --> 00:40:46.683
By changing that color variable to black,
that could also solve this issue.

00:40:49.529 --> 00:40:52.890
That's essentially
the way you would create a child theme.

00:40:52.919 --> 00:40:57.559
Search for very specific CSS selectors
or classes and see where those are

00:40:57.560 --> 00:41:01.520
in the parent theme, and then try to make
changes to see if you can get it to work.

